---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Pilgrimage">
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
        <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900">Pilgrimage Programs Before and After the Retreat</h1>
        <p class="mb-2 text-lg leading-8 text-neutral-700">
            <strong>(Optional)</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="mb-10 text-lg leading-8 text-neutral-700">Dates: December 24, 2026 – December 27, 2026 and January 4, 2027 – January 12, 2027</p>

        <div id="image-modal" class="fixed inset-0 z-50 hidden items-center justify-center bg-black/80 p-4">
            <button
                id="image-modal-close"
                type="button"
                class="absolute right-4 top-4 rounded-full bg-white/90 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900"
                aria-label="Close image"
            >
                Close
            </button>
            <img id="image-modal-img" src="" alt="" class="max-h-[90vh] max-w-[95vw] rounded-2xl object-contain" />
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-6 text-neutral-800">
            <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 bg-neutral-50 p-6">
                <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">General Introduction</h2>
                <p class="leading-8 text-neutral-700">
                    The pilgrimage programs before and after the retreat are optional journeys for practitioners who wish to return to the sacred sites closely
                    associated with the life of the Buddha.
                </p>

                <p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-neutral-700">
                    The four-day pilgrimage before the retreat will lead participants through sacred places connected with important stages in the Buddha’s
                    life: from the period of ascetic practice, the turning point toward the Middle Way, the place of enlightenment, major teaching sites, and
                    the final landmarks before his Parinirvana.
                </p>

                <p class="mt-4 leading-8 text-neutral-700">
                    After the retreat, the next journey, organized and led by Venerable Thich Hanh Tan, will take participants back to the more ancient Buddhist
                    history of Nepal, visiting Lumbini Garden, Kapilavastu, and places associated with the Buddha’s early life.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 bg-neutral-50 p-6">
                <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">4-Day Pilgrimage Program Before the Retreat</h2>

                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Day 1 – December 24</h3>
                        <p class="mb-4 font-medium text-neutral-800">Dungeshwari – Sujata – Bodh Gaya</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-6 leading-7 text-neutral-700">
                            <li>
                                <strong>Dungeshwari Cave</strong><br />
                                The place where the Buddha practiced severe asceticism for many years before realizing that extreme self-mortification does not lead
                                to awakening.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/Dungeshwari.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/Dungeshwari.png"
                                        alt="Dungeshwari Cave"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                                <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/hangdong1.jpeg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/hangdong1.jpeg"
                                            alt="Dungeshwari Cave"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/hangdong2.jpeg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/hangdong2.jpeg"
                                            alt="Dungeshwari Cave"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Sujata Stupa</strong><br />
                                A reminder of the important turning point when Sujata offered milk-rice, marking the Buddha’s shift from extreme asceticism to the
                                Middle Way.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/Sujata.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/Sujata.png"
                                        alt="Sujata Stupa"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/thapsujata.jpg" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/thapsujata.jpg"
                                        alt="Sujata Stupa"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Mahabodhi Temple Complex</strong><br />
                                The place where the Buddha attained enlightenment beneath the Bodhi Tree, one of the most sacred sites in all of Buddhism.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/Mahabodhi.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/Mahabodhi.png"
                                        alt="Mahabodhi Temple Complex"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                                <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/bodedaotrang1.jpeg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/bodedaotrang1.jpeg"
                                            alt="Mahabodhi Temple Complex"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/bodedaotrang2.jpeg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/bodedaotrang2.jpeg"
                                            alt="Mahabodhi Temple Complex"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold">Day 2 – December 25</h3>
                        <p class="mb-4 font-medium text-neutral-800">Rajgir – Vulture Peak – Nalanda University</p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-6 leading-7 text-neutral-700">
                            <li>
                                <strong>Early departure for Rajgir</strong><br />
                                A region closely connected with the period when the Buddha was actively teaching after enlightenment.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/Rajgir.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/Rajgir.png"
                                        alt="Rajgir"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/suong.jpeg" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/suong.jpeg"
                                        alt="Rajgir"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Vulture Peak (Gridhrakuta)</strong><br />
                                One of the places the Buddha often visited and taught. It is a particularly meaningful stop for meditation and Dharma reflection.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/Gridhrakuta.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
                                        src="/images/hanhhuong/Gridhrakuta.png"
                                        alt="Vulture Peak"
                                        class="mt-4 h-96 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                    />
                                </a>
                                <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/linhthuu.jpg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/linhthuu.jpg"
                                            alt="Vulture Peak"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                    <a href="/images/hanhhuong/new-gridhakuta.jpg" class="popup-image block">
                                        <img
                                            src="/images/hanhhuong/new-gridhakuta.jpg"
                                            alt="Vulture Peak"
                                            class="h-72 w-full rounded-2xl object-cover transition hover:opacity-95"
                                        />
                                    </a>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Nalanda University Ruins</strong><br />
                                A renowned center of Buddhist learning and practice that flourished for centuries, preserving a brilliant legacy of Buddhist scholarship.
                                <a href="/images/hanhhuong/nalanda.png" class="popup-image block">
                                    <img
